<HL>
   Offer for Norton Is Extended
</HL>
<DATE>
07/06/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A8
</SO>
<CO>
   F.STG NRT
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
INDUSTRIAL EQUIPMENT, MACHINE TOOLS (IND)
</IN>
<LP>
   PARIS -- Compagnie de Saint-Gobain S.A. extended the
expiration date of its $90-a-share tender offer for Norton
Co. to July 17 from today.
   In April, Saint-Gobain agreed to acquire Norton for about
$1.9 billion, topping a $75-a-share acquisition proposal from
hostile suitor BTR PLC.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   As of July 3, approximately 9.5 million shares, or 45.42%
of Norton's common stock, had been tendered to Saint-Gobain.
</TEXT>
